{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:13:50.480561+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 182, "prompt_tokens": 3852, "total_tokens": 4034, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 120, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3008, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0001775424, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001265824, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 5.096e-05}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780874027-CA9ZforLnYMYh6wXkUn6", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea45d-2270-7c23-ae07-5fafcb635d10-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C01_A01", "path": "src/ratelimit_redis/limiter.py"}, "id": "call_eace4eee6bd84b398eeb8c6b", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3852, "output_tokens": 182, "total_tokens": 4034, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3008}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 120}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:13:51.342035+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 3b0f2572474ab4ac8636eb4d2b4974a3159686d8)", "id": "lc_3ea4956a-e3b3-4cba-af16-a7614fe158b4"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Token-bucket rate limiter backed by a Redis Lua script.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom importlib import resources\nfrom typing import Tuple\n\nimport redis\n\n\n_SCRIPT = resources.files(\"ratelimit_redis\").joinpath(\"bucket.lua\").read_text()\n\n\nclass Limiter:\n    def __init__(self, redis_url: str, capacity: int, refill_per_sec: float) -> None:\n        self._r = redis.Redis.from_url(redis_url, decode_responses=False)\n        self._capacity = capacity\n        self._refill = refill_per_sec\n        self._sha = self._r.script_load(_SCRIPT)\n\n    def check(self, key: str, cost: int = 1) -> Tuple[bool, int]:\n        bucket_key = f\"rl:{{{key}}}\"  # hash-tag for cluster compatibility\n        result = self._r.evalsha(\n            self._sha,\n            1,\n            bucket_key,\n            str(self._capacity),\n            str(self._refill),\n            str(cost),\n        )\n        allowed = bool(result[0])\n        remaining = int(result[1])\n        return allowed, remaining\n", "id": "lc_ae065a14-e9ff-460a-97b8-d9ff7fdc1dc0"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "a63c2797-adab-4cd3-b0c9-06ad6a4d04aa", "tool_call_id": "call_eace4eee6bd84b398eeb8c6b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:13:54.406582+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 89, "prompt_tokens": 4206, "total_tokens": 4295, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 28, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3840, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 8.6912e-05, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 6.1992e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 2.492e-05}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780874031-l9uj0qge4eaydceIeHbR", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea45d-30ef-7fa2-984b-915dfbfed179-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"path": "src/ratelimit_redis/bucket.lua", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T12_R01_C01_A01"}, "id": "call_49736bec252946e2b3f0a307", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4206, "output_tokens": 89, "total_tokens": 4295, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 3840}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 28}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:13:55.183030+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4da3d6885a07f9cd566156eb36f67e10f35e2e53)", "id": "lc_2d44ebeb-ca3c-48fd-88b7-93223d9fbdcb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "-- bucket.lua: atomic token-bucket consume.\n-- KEYS[1]   = bucket key\n-- ARGV[1]   = capacity\n-- ARGV[2]   = refill per second (note: rounded down to nearest integer per call)\n-- ARGV[3]   = cost\n--\n-- The function returns {allowed (0/1), remaining tokens (int)}.\n--\n-- Stored state at KEYS[1] is a hash with fields:\n--   tokens : last observed bucket level (integer count, stored as string)\n--   ts     : Redis-server wall clock at last update (ms, integer)\n--\n-- Note on refill semantics: although the constructor accepts a float\n-- refill_per_sec, the Lua side rounds the per-call refill increment\n-- down to an integer. This is a deliberate choice to make the\n-- algorithm easier to reason about; sub-token refill is therefore\n-- effectively quantized to 1-token-per-elapsed-second.\n--\n-- Atomicity: this script runs as a single Redis command (EVALSHA), so\n-- the refill + consume sequence is not interleaved with any other\n-- client's evalsha against the same key.\n\nlocal key      = KEYS[1]\nlocal capacity = tonumber(ARGV[1])\nlocal refill   = tonumber(ARGV[2])\nlocal cost     = tonumber(ARGV[3])\n\nlocal now_ms = redis.call(\"TIME\")\nnow_ms = now_ms[1] * 1000 + math.floor(now_ms[2] / 1000)\n\nlocal state = redis.call(\"HMGET\", key, \"tokens\", \"ts\")\nlocal tokens = tonumber(state[1])\nlocal last_ts = tonumber(state[2])\n\nif tokens == nil or last_ts == nil then\n    tokens = capacity\n    last_ts = now_ms\nend\n\nlocal elapsed_sec = math.max(0, (now_ms - last_ts) / 1000.0)\ntokens = math.min(capacity, tokens + elapsed_sec * refill)\n\nlocal allowed = 0\nif tokens >= cost then\n    tokens = tokens - cost\n    allowed = 1\nend\n\nredis.call(\"HMSET\", key, \"tokens\", tostring(tokens), \"ts\", tostring(now_ms))\n-- Set TTL so unused buckets expire (10x time to fully refill, plus a floor)\nlocal ttl = math.max(60, math.ceil(capacity / refill * 10))\nredis.call(\"EXPIRE\", key, ttl)\n\nreturn {allowed, math.floor(tokens)}\n", "id": "lc_e89d48db-dc7c-4b22-9366-be95d9ca8c0e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "c4af2b37-2158-4e50-81a3-6fe571d30503", "tool_call_id": "call_49736bec252946e2b3f0a307", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:14:08.253510+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a step-by-step walkthrough of `Limiter.check()` and what happens on the Redis side.\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\n```python\ndef check(self, key: str, cost: int = 1) -> Tuple[bool, int]:\n```\n\n| Parameter | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `key` | The rate-limit subject (e.g. a user ID or IP). |\n| `cost` | How many tokens to deduct (default `1`). |\n| *(closure)* `self._capacity` | Maximum tokens the bucket can hold, set at construction. |\n| *(closure)* `self._refill` | Tokens replenished per second, set at construction. |\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-step\n\n### 1. Build the Redis key\n```python\nbucket_key = f\"rl:{{{key}}}\"\n```\nThe curly braces are a **Redis hash-tag** (`rl:{<key>}`). This ensures all keys with the same user sit on the same shard in a Redis Cluster.\n\n### 2. Execute the Lua script atomically via `EVALSHA`\n```python\nresult = self._r.evalsha(self._sha, 1, bucket_key,\n                         str(self._capacity), str(self._refill), str(cost))\n```\nA pre-loaded Lua script (`bucket.lua`) is sent as a **single atomic Redis command**. No other client's script can interleave between the read and the write steps below.\n\n### 3. Inside the Lua script (`bucket.lua`)\n\n| Step | What happens | Redis command used |\n|------|-------------|--------------------|\n| **3a. Get server time** | `TIME` → `now_ms` (milliseconds). Uses the Redis server's clock, not the client's. | `redis.call(\"TIME\")` |\n| **3b. Read current state** | `HMGET key \"tokens\" \"ts\"` — reads the last-known token count and the timestamp of the last update. | `redis.call(\"HMGET\", ...)` |\n| **3c. First-ever call for this key?** | If `tokens` or `ts` are `nil`, the bucket is initialised to `capacity` tokens with `ts = now`. | *(none — just Lua locals)* |\n| **3d. Refill** | `elapsed_sec = (now - last_ts) / 1000`. Then: `tokens = min(capacity, tokens + elapsed_sec * refill)`. The refill is **rounded down to whole tokens** (the comment notes the float is truncated to an integer per call). | *(computation only)* |\n| **3e. Consume** | If `tokens >= cost`, subtract `cost` and set `allowed = 1`. Otherwise `allowed = 0` and nothing is deducted. | *(computation only)* |\n| **3f. Persist new state** | `HMSET key \"tokens\" <new_tokens> \"ts\" <now_ms>` — overwrites the hash with the updated bucket level and current timestamp. | `redis.call(\"HMSET\", ...)` |\n| **3g. Set / refresh TTL** | `EXPIRE key ttl` where `ttl = max(60, ceil(capacity / refill * 10))`. This is roughly 10× the time it takes to refill from empty to full (or a minimum of 60 seconds). Prevents unbounded key growth for inactive subjects. | `redis.call(\"EXPIRE\", ...)` |\n\n### 4. Return to the caller\n\nThe script returns a two-element array `{allowed, floor(tokens)}`.\n\nBack in Python this becomes:\n```python\nallowed  = bool(result[0])   # True  = request granted\nremaining = int(result[1])   # tokens left after this call\n```\n\n**Return type:** `Tuple[bool, int]` — `(allowed, remaining)`.\n\n---\n\n## Side effects on Redis\n\n1. **A Redis hash at `rl:{<key>}` is created or updated** with two fields:\n   - `tokens` (string) — the current token count after refill and possible consumption.\n   - `ts` (string) — the Redis-server wall-clock time in milliseconds of this call.\n2. **A TTL is (re)set** on that key to `max(60, ceil(capacity / refill * 10))` seconds, so the bucket auto-expires if untouched.\n\nThere are **no other side effects** — no lists, no pub/sub, no transactions beyond this single atomic `EVALSHA`.\n\n---\n\n## A couple of quirks worth noting\n\n- **Integer quantisation of refill:** Even though `refill_per_sec` is a float, the Lua script multiplies elapsed seconds by it and then stores the result via `math.floor(tokens)` — meaning sub-token replenishment is effectively lost each second. If your rate is e.g. `0.5` tokens/sec, you'd only gain a token every 2 seconds, not continuously.\n- **Clock dependency:** The script relies on `TIME` from the Redis server. In a clustered environment all nodes should have synchronised clocks (NTP) for consistent behaviour.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1096, "prompt_tokens": 4848, "total_tokens": 5944, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 16, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4160, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000414848, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000107968, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00030688}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780874035-2bb81DuDPqvOOgTp7MvS", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea45d-3ff0-7cf2-8892-d49ea87b6531-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4848, "output_tokens": 1096, "total_tokens": 5944, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4160}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 16}}}}]}}}
